<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
  <title>How It Works — Jamie Forrester</title>
  <meta
    name="description"
    content="How diagnostic and redesign engagements work, from first email to written delivery."
  />
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.png" />

  <!-- IBM Plex Sans + Mono -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />

  <style>
    :root{
      --bg:#0b0b0c;
      --panel:#101114;
      --panel-soft:#0d0e11;

      --text-main:#f1f3f5;
      --text-dim:#c3c8d0;
      --text-faint:#8b93a1;

      --border:#232731;
      --border-soft:rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      --accent:#343a46;

      --label-blue:#4aa3ff;
      --cta-blue:#5ab0ff;

      --focus-ring:rgba(255,255,255,0.95);
      --focus-bg:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);

      --radius-sm:10px;
      --radius-md:14px;
      --radius-lg:16px;

      --shadow-soft:0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.24);
      --shadow-hover:0 0 0 1px rgba(90,176,255,0.10), 0 14px 38px rgba(0,0,0,0.28);
    }

    *{box-sizing:border-box;}
    html{color-scheme:dark;}

    body{
      margin:0;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(90,176,255,0.035), transparent 28%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, #0b0b0c, #0b0b0c);
      color:var(--text-main);
      font-family:"IBM Plex Sans", ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      line-height:1.65;
      font-size:16px;
      -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;
      text-rendering:optimizeLegibility;
      font-feature-settings:"ss01" 1, "cv05" 1;
    }

    .wrap{
      max-width:1120px;
      margin:0 auto;
      padding:64px 24px 56px;
    }

    .mono,
    .sub,
    .pill,
    .label,
    .label-note,
    .eyebrow,
    .btn,
    .skip-link,
    .meta-chip,
    .phase-index,
    .flow-label{
      font-family:"IBM Plex Mono", ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
    }

    .skip-link{
      position:absolute;
      left:12px;
      top:10px;
      padding:10px 12px;
      border-radius:10px;
      border:1px solid var(--accent);
      background:var(--panel);
      color:#fff;
      transform:translateY(-200%);
      transition:transform 120ms ease;
      z-index:9999;
      text-decoration:none;
      font-size:12px;
    }
    .skip-link:focus-visible{
      transform:translateY(0);
      outline:2px solid var(--focus-ring);
      outline-offset:3px;
    }

    a{
      color:#fff;
      text-decoration:none;
      border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);
      padding-bottom:1px;
      transition:border-color 140ms ease, background-color 140ms ease, color 140ms ease, transform 140ms ease;
    }
    a:hover{
      border-bottom-color:#fff;
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    }
    a:focus-visible{
      outline:2px solid var(--focus-ring);
      outline-offset:3px;
      border-bottom-color:transparent;
      background:var(--focus-bg);
      border-radius:6px;
    }

    .btn{
      display:inline-flex;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:center;
      gap:10px;
      padding:10px 14px;
      border-radius:12px;
      border:1px solid var(--accent);
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.018);
      color:#fff;
      font-size:13px;
      font-weight:500;
      text-decoration:none;
      line-height:1;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      letter-spacing:0.06em;
      white-space:nowrap;
      transition:
        transform 140ms ease,
        background-color 140ms ease,
        border-color 140ms ease,
        box-shadow 140ms ease;
    }
    .btn:hover{
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      transform:translateY(-1px);
    }
    .btn:focus-visible{
      outline:2px solid var(--focus-ring);
      outline-offset:3px;
      background:var(--focus-bg);
    }

    .btn-primary{
      color:var(--cta-blue);
      border-color:rgba(90,176,255,0.30);
      background:rgba(90,176,255,0.075);
      box-shadow:inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    }
    .btn-primary:hover{
      background:rgba(90,176,255,0.12);
      border-color:rgba(90,176,255,0.45);
      box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.18);
    }

    .btn-current{
      border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      color:var(--text-dim);
      cursor:default;
      pointer-events:none;
    }

    header{
      display:flex;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:space-between;
      gap:20px;
      padding-bottom:24px;
      border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-soft);
      margin-bottom:24px;
    }

    .h-left{
      display:flex;
      align-items:center;
      gap:18px;
      min-width:0;
    }

    .h-ident{
      min-width:0;
    }

    .avatar-link{
      display:inline-flex;
      border-bottom:none;
      border-radius:999px;
      flex:0 0 auto;
    }
    .avatar-link:hover{
      background:transparent;
      transform:translateY(-1px);
    }
    .avatar-link:focus-visible{
      background:transparent;
      outline:2px solid var(--focus-ring);
      outline-offset:4px;
      border-radius:999px;
    }

    .avatar{
      width:78px;
      height:78px;
      border-radius:999px;
      border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10);
      object-fit:cover;
      filter:grayscale(100%);
      flex:0 0 auto;
      box-shadow:0 6px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.18);
      display:block;
    }

    h1{
      margin:0;
      font-size:clamp(1.1rem, 1rem + 0.7vw, 1.45rem);
      font-weight:600;
      letter-spacing:-0.03em;
      line-height:1.15;
    }

    .sub{
      margin-top:6px;
      font-size:11px;
      color:var(--text-dim);
      text-transform:uppercase;
      letter-spacing:0.14em;
      white-space:nowrap;
    }

    .meta-row-top{
      margin-top:12px;
    }

    .pill{
      display:-webkit-inline-box;
      -webkit-line-clamp:2;
      -webkit-box-orient:vertical;
      overflow:hidden;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:center;
      padding:8px 12px;
      width:392px;
      border-radius:12px;
      border:1px solid var(--border);
      background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.018), rgba(255,255,255,0.01));
      color:var(--text-dim);
      font-size:11px;
      letter-spacing:0.05em;
      line-height:1.35;
      white-space:normal;
    }

    .top-links{
      display:flex;
      gap:10px;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      justify-content:flex-end;
      align-items:center;
    }

    .hero{
      border:1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius:var(--radius-lg);
      padding:28px;
      background:
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.02), rgba(255,255,255,0.00)),
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(90,176,255,0.018), rgba(255,255,255,0));
      box-shadow:var(--shadow-soft);
      margin-bottom:24px;
      transition:border-color 160ms ease, box-shadow 160ms ease, transform 160ms ease;
    }
    .hero:hover{
      border-color:rgba(90,176,255,0.18);
      box-shadow:var(--shadow-hover);
      transform:translateY(-1px);
    }

    .hero-grid{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:1.05fr 0.95fr;
      gap:24px;
      align-items:stretch;
    }

    .eyebrow{
      color:var(--label-blue);
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:0.18em;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      margin:0 0 10px;
    }

    .hero h2{
      margin:0 0 14px;
      font-size:clamp(1.7rem, 1.35rem + 1.1vw, 2.35rem);
      line-height:1.14;
      letter-spacing:-0.04em;
      font-weight:700;
      max-width:15ch;
    }

    .hero p{
      margin:0 0 12px;
      color:#d8dde4;
      font-size:clamp(0.98rem, 0.94rem + 0.15vw, 1.05rem);
      max-width:70ch;
    }

    .hero strong{
      color:#fff;
      font-weight:600;
    }

    .hero-actions{
      display:flex;
      gap:12px;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      align-items:center;
      margin-top:18px;
    }

    .flow-card{
      border:1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius:16px;
      padding:18px;
      background:
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.02), rgba(255,255,255,0.008));
      box-shadow:var(--shadow-soft);
      min-height:100%;
      display:flex;
      flex-direction:column;
    }

    .flow-card-head{
      padding-bottom:12px;
      margin-bottom:12px;
      border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-soft);
    }

    .flow-label{
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:0.16em;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      color:var(--label-blue);
      margin-bottom:6px;
    }

    .flow-sub{
      font-size:11px;
      color:var(--text-faint);
      letter-spacing:0.04em;
    }

    .flow-list{
      display:grid;
      gap:10px;
    }

    .flow-step{
      border:1px solid var(--border-soft);
      border-radius:12px;
      padding:12px;
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.01);
    }

    .flow-step strong{
      display:block;
      font-size:13px;
      color:#fff;
      margin-bottom:4px;
    }

    .flow-step span{
      font-size:13px;
      color:var(--text-dim);
      line-height:1.55;
    }

    .grid{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
      gap:24px;
      align-items:start;
    }

    .card{
      background:
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.015), rgba(255,255,255,0.008));
      border:1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius:var(--radius-md);
      padding:22px;
      box-shadow:var(--shadow-soft);
      transition:border-color 160ms ease, box-shadow 160ms ease, transform 160ms ease;
    }
    .card:hover{
      border-color:rgba(90,176,255,0.18);
      box-shadow:var(--shadow-hover);
      transform:translateY(-1px);
    }
    .card + .card{margin-top:24px;}

    .label-row{
      display:flex;
      align-items:baseline;
      justify-content:space-between;
      gap:12px;
      border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-soft);
      padding-bottom:12px;
      margin-bottom:16px;
    }

    .label{
      font-size:11px;
      font-weight:600;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      letter-spacing:0.16em;
      color:var(--label-blue);
    }

    .label-note{
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:0.08em;
      text-transform:lowercase;
      color:var(--label-blue);
      white-space:nowrap;
    }

    .section-title{
      margin:0 0 14px;
      font-size:1.15rem;
      font-weight:600;
      line-height:1.25;
      letter-spacing:-0.02em;
    }

    p{
      margin:0 0 14px;
      color:var(--text-dim);
    }

    .lead{
      color:#d7dce3;
      font-size:15px;
      line-height:1.7;
    }

    .meta-row{
      display:flex;
      gap:10px;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      margin:0 0 16px;
    }

    .meta-chip{
      display:inline-flex;
      align-items:center;
      gap:8px;
      padding:8px 10px;
      border-radius:10px;
      border:1px solid var(--border);
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.015);
      color:var(--text-dim);
      font-size:11px;
      letter-spacing:0.08em;
      text-transform:uppercase;
    }

    .phase-list{
      display:grid;
      gap:14px;
    }

    .phase{
      border:1px solid var(--border-soft);
      border-radius:12px;
      padding:14px;
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.01);
    }

    .phase-head{
      display:flex;
      align-items:baseline;
      gap:10px;
      margin-bottom:8px;
    }

    .phase-index{
      font-size:10px;
      letter-spacing:0.12em;
      color:var(--label-blue);
      text-transform:uppercase;
      min-width:22px;
    }

    .phase-title{
      font-size:14px;
      font-weight:600;
      color:#fff;
      letter-spacing:-0.01em;
    }

    .phase p{
      margin:0;
      font-size:14px;
      color:var(--text-dim);
      line-height:1.62;
    }

    .split-list{
      display:grid;
      gap:14px;
    }

    .mini{
      border:1px solid var(--border-soft);
      border-radius:12px;
      padding:14px;
      background:rgba(255,255,255,0.01);
    }

    .mini h3{
      margin:0 0 8px;
      font-size:14px;
      font-weight:600;
      color:#fff;
      letter-spacing:-0.01em;
    }

    .mini p{
      margin:0;
      font-size:14px;
      color:var(--text-dim);
      line-height:1.62;
    }

    .section-block{
      margin-top:16px;
    }

    .section-head{
      margin:0 0 10px;
      font-size:14px;
      font-weight:600;
      color:#fff;
      letter-spacing:-0.01em;
    }

    ul.clean{
      margin:0;
      padding:0;
      list-style:none;
      display:grid;
      gap:10px;
    }
    ul.clean li{
      padding-left:16px;
      position:relative;
      color:#d7dce3;
      font-size:14px;
      line-height:1.62;
    }
    ul.clean li::before{
      content:"→";
      position:absolute;
      left:0;
      color:var(--text-faint);
    }

    .cta-bar{
      margin-top:24px;
      padding-top:18px;
      border-top:1px solid var(--border-soft);
      display:flex;
      gap:12px;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      align-items:center;
    }

    footer{
      margin-top:32px;
      padding-top:18px;
      border-top:1px solid var(--border-soft);
      display:flex;
      justify-content:space-between;
      gap:12px;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      color:var(--text-faint);
      font-size:12px;
    }

    .footer-links{
      display:flex;
      gap:14px;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      align-items:center;
    }

    @media (max-width: 920px){
      .wrap{padding-top:48px;}
      header{
        flex-direction:column;
        align-items:flex-start;
        gap:16px;
      }
      .top-links{justify-content:flex-start;}
      .hero-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}
      .grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}
      .pill{width:100%;}
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce){
      *{
        scroll-behavior:auto !important;
        transition:none !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <a class="skip-link" href="#main">Skip to content</a>

  <div class="wrap">
    <header>
      <div class="h-left">
        <a class="avatar-link" href="./index.html" aria-label="Back to home">
          <img src="./jamie-forrester-profile.png" alt="Jamie Forrester" class="avatar" />
        </a>

        <div class="h-ident">
          <h1>Jamie Forrester</h1>
          <div class="sub">Independent Systems Architect</div>
          <div class="meta-row-top">
            <span class="pill" aria-label="Positioning">A fixed process from failure pattern to decision-ready document</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="top-links" aria-label="Primary links">
        <a class="btn" href="./services.html">SERVICES</a>
        <span class="btn btn-current" aria-current="page">HOW IT WORKS</span>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:hello@jamieforrester.com?subject=Diagnostic%20Request%3A%20%5BSystem%20Name%5D">EMAIL</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="hero" aria-label="How it works overview">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">How it works</div>
          <h2>From first email to a usable internal document.</h2>
          <p>
            This page explains exactly how an engagement works: what you send, how fit is assessed,
            how the work is conducted, and what you receive at the end.
          </p>
          <p>
            The process is fixed, written-first, and designed to reduce ambiguity. No slide decks.
            No meeting chain by default. No open-ended advisory drift.
          </p>
          <p>
            You send a <strong>Five-Line Brief</strong>. I determine whether the work should begin with
            <strong>Diagnostic</strong> or move directly to <strong>Redesign</strong>. If the fit is correct,
            I return one structured written artifact for decision owners and builders.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:hello@jamieforrester.com?subject=Diagnostic%20Request%3A%20%5BSystem%20Name%5D">EMAIL</a>
            <a class="btn" href="./services.html">VIEW SERVICES</a>
            <a class="btn" href="./index.html">BACK TO HOME</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-card" aria-label="Process summary">
          <div class="flow-card-head">
            <div class="flow-label">Process Summary</div>
            <div class="flow-sub">The path from entry to delivery</div>
          </div>

          <div class="flow-list">
            <div class="flow-step">
              <strong>01 — Five-Line Brief</strong>
              <span>You send the failure pattern, stake, interfaces, concentration, constraints, plus any relevant materials.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flow-step">
              <strong>02 — Fit Assessment</strong>
              <span>I determine whether the issue is a fit, and whether the correct entry point is Diagnostic or Redesign.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flow-step">
              <strong>03 — Fixed Scope</strong>
              <span>The engagement boundary is confirmed before work begins. The process does not expand by default.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flow-step">
              <strong>04 — Written Delivery</strong>
              <span>You receive one structured document designed for internal circulation, decision-making, and builder handoff.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flow-step">
              <strong>05 — Clarification</strong>
              <span>One minor clarification pass is included. New analysis or widened scope becomes new work.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <main id="main" class="grid" role="main">
      <section>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="label-row">
            <span class="label">01 // Working protocol</span>
            <span class="label-note">how we interact</span>
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">Written-first, asynchronous, and bounded.</h2>

          <div class="meta-row">
            <span class="meta-chip">written-first</span>
            <span class="meta-chip">async by default</span>
            <span class="meta-chip">fixed process</span>
          </div>

          <p class="lead">
            Most of the work is conducted through written exchange and artifact review. I do not move into your workflow,
            join your Slack, or begin with a chain of meetings. The point is to preserve structural objectivity and keep the process efficient.
          </p>

          <div class="split-list">
            <div class="mini">
              <h3>Default mode</h3>
              <p>
                The default mode is email, document review, and written clarification. This keeps the engagement focused on structural signal rather than conversational noise.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mini">
              <h3>Clarifying questions</h3>
              <p>
                If something important is missing, I may ask targeted clarifying questions. These are used to tighten scope and locate the real boundary, not to create a meeting cycle.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mini">
              <h3>What this prevents</h3>
              <p>
                This protocol is designed to prevent premature implementation, endless alignment calls, and the slow drift that happens when the work stays verbally defined.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="label-row">
            <span class="label">02 // The process</span>
            <span class="label-note">start to finish</span>
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">A fixed sequence from intake to delivery.</h2>

          <div class="phase-list">
            <div class="phase">
              <div class="phase-head">
                <span class="phase-index">01</span>
                <span class="phase-title">Five-Line Brief</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                You begin by emailing five lines: <strong>The Pattern</strong>, <strong>The Stake</strong>,
                <strong>The Interfaces</strong>, <strong>Concentration</strong>, and <strong>Constraints</strong>.
                You can attach any materials that reflect the current state.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="phase">
              <div class="phase-head">
                <span class="phase-index">02</span>
                <span class="phase-title">Fit Assessment</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                I review the brief and the materials to determine whether the issue is structurally suited to this approach,
                whether the boundary can be clearly defined, and whether the right starting point is Diagnostic or Redesign.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="phase">
              <div class="phase-head">
                <span class="phase-index">03</span>
                <span class="phase-title">Scope Confirmation</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                If the fit is correct, the engagement is confirmed as a fixed-scope written intervention. The boundary of the work is set before analysis begins.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="phase">
              <div class="phase-head">
                <span class="phase-index">04</span>
                <span class="phase-title">Upstream Work</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                I work through the materials, locate the real operating structure, define the relevant boundary, and identify the structural implications. For redesign work, this includes the transition sequence and interface changes.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="phase">
              <div class="phase-head">
                <span class="phase-index">05</span>
                <span class="phase-title">Delivery + Clarification</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                You receive one structured written artifact for internal circulation. One minor clarification pass is included after delivery. If the boundary changes, that becomes a new engagement.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cta-bar">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:hello@jamieforrester.com?subject=Diagnostic%20Request%3A%20%5BSystem%20Name%5D">EMAIL</a>
            <a class="btn" href="./services.html">VIEW SERVICES</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="label-row">
            <span class="label">03 // What you provide</span>
            <span class="label-note">client inputs</span>
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">Useful signal, not polished presentation.</h2>

          <p class="lead">
            You do not need a perfect brief. You do need to send enough signal to make the real pattern visible.
            Rough materials are acceptable if they reflect what is actually happening.
          </p>

          <div class="section-block">
            <h3 class="section-head">What to send</h3>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>A completed Five-Line Brief</li>
              <li>Diagrams, policies, workflows, notes, contracts, screenshots, post-mortems, or internal documents</li>
              <li>A clear statement of known constraints: technical, legal, budgetary, or operational</li>
              <li>Timely written responses if clarifying questions are required</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="section-block">
            <h3 class="section-head">What matters most</h3>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>Accuracy over polish</li>
              <li>Real operating reality over official narrative</li>
              <li>Boundary signal over volume</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="label-row">
            <span class="label">04 // Which route applies</span>
            <span class="label-note">diagnostic vs redesign</span>
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">Not every system starts in the same place.</h2>

          <div class="split-list">
            <div class="mini">
              <h3>Start with Diagnostic</h3>
              <p>
                Begin with Diagnostic when the real structure is still unclear, the failure keeps recurring under different names,
                or the team is still arguing about what is actually breaking.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mini">
              <h3>Start with Redesign</h3>
              <p>
                Move directly to Redesign when the failure mode is already obvious, the boundary is already visible,
                and the real bottleneck is lack of a clear transition sequence.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mini">
              <h3>How the decision is made</h3>
              <p>
                The Five-Line Brief exists partly to answer this question. If the correct route is unclear from the outside, I determine it during fit assessment.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="label-row">
            <span class="label">05 // What you receive</span>
            <span class="label-note">the deliverable</span>
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">A structured document, not a deck.</h2>

          <p class="lead">
            Every engagement ends with one written artifact designed for internal use. It is intended to be read,
            circulated, and handed directly to the people who need to make decisions or execute against it.
          </p>

          <div class="section-block">
            <h3 class="section-head">What the artifact is for</h3>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>Internal decision-making</li>
              <li>Builder handoff</li>
              <li>Boundary clarification</li>
              <li>Reducing debate about what changes first</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="section-block">
            <h3 class="section-head">What it is not</h3>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>Not a slide deck</li>
              <li>Not a workshop or facilitation package</li>
              <li>Not implementation execution</li>
              <li>Not an open-ended advisory retainer</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="label-row">
            <span class="label">06 // When it is not a fit</span>
            <span class="label-note">clear refusal logic</span>
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">Not every problem belongs in this process.</h2>

          <ul class="clean">
            <li>The issue is too broad or too undefined for a bounded written intervention</li>
            <li>The real need is implementation ownership, delivery leadership, or ongoing facilitation</li>
            <li>The available inputs do not contain enough signal to define a reliable boundary</li>
            <li>The failure is primarily operational noise rather than a structural problem</li>
            <li>Multiple unrelated failure modes are being combined into one request</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="section-block">
            <h3 class="section-head">What happens then</h3>
            <p>
              If it is not a fit, I say so. The point of the intake is to determine whether this approach is appropriate, not to force every problem into the same engagement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="label-row">
            <span class="label">07 // After delivery</span>
            <span class="label-note">what happens next</span>
          </div>

          <div class="split-list">
            <div class="mini">
              <h3>Included</h3>
              <p>
                One minor clarification pass is included after delivery. This covers clarification of the document as delivered, not new analysis or widened scope.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mini">
              <h3>New engagement threshold</h3>
              <p>
                If the boundary expands, the problem changes shape, or deeper analysis is required, that becomes new work and requires a separate engagement.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mini">
              <h3>How to start</h3>
              <p>
                The entry route is always the same: send the Five-Line Brief, attach anything useful, and I will determine whether there is a fit and where the work should begin.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

